I need to identify the amount of profit the entity retains after all expenses (Net Profit) along with 5 component sub-items that contribute to this calculation.

From the income statement, I can see that:
- Net Profit = 112375.10

Now I need to identify 5 contributing sub-items. Looking at the structure of the income statement, these could include:

1. Main Business Revenue/Total Revenue = 775598.77
2. Cost of Goods Sold/Total Cost = 496220.00
3. Total Expenses = 140961.72
4. Interest Income = 12737.96
5. Tax Expense = 38779.91

These 5 components directly factor into the calculation of Net Profit as follows:
Net Profit = Total Revenue - Total Cost - Total Expenses + Interest Income - Tax Expense
= 775598.77 - 496220.00 - 140961.72 + 12737.96 - 38779.91 = 112375.10
